I'm going to talk about being a food delivery driver, which is probably one of the jobs I would least like to do.
I first became familiar with the job when I moved to Ho Chi Minh City to pursue my studies. At that time, I was new to the city, so I often used ride-hailing apps like Grab or Gojek to get around. During those trips, I had the chance to talk with many drivers and listen to their stories.
I clearly remember one driver telling me that he didn't actually enjoy his job, but he had to continue doing it to earn a living and support his family. That conversation left a strong impression on me.
In my opinion, the job is quite challenging, both physically and mentally. Food delivery drivers have to deal with heavy traffic, the constant risk of accidents, and harsh weather conditions, all while trying to deliver orders on time. In addition, they often have to work during peak hours, such as lunchtime or in the evening, when the road are even more congested.
Another concern is the potential impact on health. Drivers spend long hours sitting, which can increase the risk of certain health problems. Morever, some may rely on energy drinks to stay awake, which can be harmful if consumed regularly. On top of that, dealing with impatient or difficult customers can make the job even more stressful.
For these reasons, I don't think I would enjoy this kind of work. Although it offers flexibility and can be a good source of income, especially as a part-time job, I would personally prefer a more stable job with fixed working hours and a healthier working environment.
